TY  - JOUR
T1  - Inventory Depletion Management When the Field Life is Random
AU  - Nahmias, Steven
Y1  - 1974/05/01
PY  - 1974
DA  - 1974/05/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.20.9.1276
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.20.9.1276
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1276
EP  - 1283
VL  - 20
IS  - 9
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper considers the problem of describing optimal issuing policies when the field life, X(s), is a nonnegative random variable. A new optimality criterion involving stochastic ordering is introduced and sufficient conditions given for the optimality of FIFO and LIFO. Two specific models of perishable inventory are then considered; Model I allows for the perishing of items in the stockpile and Model II does not. It is demonstrated that both LIFO and FIFO are optimal for Model I when the items age at the same rate in the stockpile as in the field. Under the assumption that X(s) is uniformly distributed the optimality of FIFO is established for Model II.
AB  - This paper considers the problem of describing optimal issuing policies when the field life, X(s), is a nonnegative random variable. A new optimality criterion involving stochastic ordering is introduced and sufficient conditions given for the optimality of FIFO and LIFO. Two specific models of perishable inventory are then considered; Model I allows for the perishing of items in the stockpile and Model II does not. It is demonstrated that both LIFO and FIFO are optimal for Model I when the items age at the same rate in the stockpile as in the field. Under the assumption that X(s) is uniformly distributed the optimality of FIFO is established for Model II.
